{{BLP sources|date=January 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Jarosław Jach | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Jarosław Przemysław Jach<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|2|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Bielawa]], Poland | height = 1.92 m | position = [[Centre back]] | currentclub = [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] (on loan from [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]) | clubnumber = 7 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Pogoń Pieszyce | youthyears2 = 2009–2011 | youthclubs2 = Lechia Dzierżoniów | years1 = 2011–2013 | caps1 = 20 | goals1 = 1 | clubs1 = Lechia Dzierżoniów | years2 = 2013–2018 | caps2 = 68 | goals2 = 4 | clubs2 = [[Zagłębie Lubin]] | years3 = 2018– | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0 | clubs3 = [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] | years4 = 2018–2019 | caps4 = 5 | goals4 = 0 | clubs4 = → [[Çaykur Rizespor]] (loan) | years5 = 2019– | caps5 = 0 | goals5 = 0 | clubs5 = → [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] (loan) | nationalyears1 = 2015–2017 | nationalteam1 = [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 14 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | nationalyears2 = 2017– | nationalteam2 = [[Poland national football team|Poland]] | nationalcaps2 = 2 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | club-update = 00:44, 25 September 2018 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 13 November 2017 }} '''Jarosław Przemysław Jach''' (born 17 February 1994) is a Polish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre back]] for [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] of the [[Moldovan National Division]], on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] from {{English football updater|CrystalP}} club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].
==Club career== ===Early career=== Although his mother Lucyna originally wanted him to be a swimmer, young Jarosław always was more of a football fan.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}} He started his career in a local club [[Pogoń Pieszyce]], where he played until his friend helped him earn a transfer to [[Lechia Dzierżoniów]]. With time he established himself as one of the most important figures in the club and was often chosen as [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the team and took [[Direct free kick|free kicks]] even though he wasn't even 20 years old.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}
===Zagłębie Lubin=== He signed with [[Zagłębie Lubin]] in 2013 and after a year of playing in the reserve team, he made his debut in Polish top division on May 27, 2014 against [[Podbeskidzie Bielsko-Biała]], coming on as substitute for [[Đorđe Čotra]] in 74th minute of the match.
The club eventually got relegated and started the 2014–15 season in second division. Jach made 13 appearances, helping the side to promotion.
In 2015–16 season, he scored his first goal in a 2-1 win over Podbeskidzie Bielsko-Biała on 22 November 2015. He helped his team to win a bronze medal in that season.
In the 2016–17 season and the departure of [[Maciej Dąbrowski]] to [[Legia Warsaw]], he became a regular starter for Zagłębie and proved to be a crucial part of the team's defense, which turned out to be the 5th in the league. A series of performances however, was stopped by an injury which caused him to pause for 3 months.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}
===Crystal Palace=== Jach signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 23 January 2018 on a three-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42796432|title=Jaroslaw Jach: Crystal Palace sign Poland centre-back from Zagłebie Lubin|last=|first=|date=23 January 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=23 January 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-GB}}</ref>
====Çaykur Rizespor (loan)==== In July 2018, Jach joined Turkish [[Süper Lig]] side [[Çaykur Rizespor]] on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] until the end of the 2018–19 season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/jach-moves-on-loan-to-caykur-rizespor/|title=Jach Moves on Loan to Caykur Rizespor|website=cpfc.co.uk|date=24 July 2018|accessdate=25 July 2018}}</ref> though his loan was ended early, in February 2019, after he made only five league appearances for the side.
====Sheriff Tiraspol (loan)==== Following his departure from Rizespor, Jach joined Moldovan side [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canalplus.pl/sport/news-jaroslaw-jach-w-sheriffie_781038|title=Jarosław Jach w Sheriffie (2019/02/02)|website=www.canalplus.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fc-sheriff.com/en/vse/welcome-jaroslaw/|title=Welcome, Jaroslaw|website=FC Sheriff|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref>
